<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="label2rgb" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><refnamediv><refname>label2rgb</refname><refpurpose>Convert labels to a uint8 RGB image.</refpurpose></refnamediv><refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>rgb = label2rgb(labels); rgb = label2rgb(labels, cmap)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>labels</term><listitem><para>Nonnegative 2D label matrix. Label 0 is background.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>cmap</term><listitem><para>Optional N-by-3 colormap in 0-to-1 or 0-to-255 scale.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>rgb</term><listitem><para>uint8 M-by-N-by-3 visualization.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection><refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>label2rgb</function> assigns each positive label a colormap row and leaves background black.</para></refsection><refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[mask = zeros(6, 6) == 1; mask(2:3, 2:3) = %t; [labels, count] = imlabel(mask); rgb = label2rgb(labels); imshow(rgb);]]></programlisting></refsection><refsection role="see also"><title>See also</title><simplelist type="inline"><member><link linkend="imlabel">imlabel</link></member><member><link linkend="ind2rgb">ind2rgb</link></member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>Authors</title><simplelist type="vert"><member>Tan Chin Luh</member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>History</title><informaltable border="1"><tr><td>Version</td><td>Description</td></tr><tr><td>5.0.0</td><td>Function introduced in development Step 3.</td></tr></informaltable></refsection></refentry>
